# Shift Ü — environment variables
# Copy to .env.local for local dev, and set the same keys in Vercel ▸ Project ▸
# Settings ▸ Environment Variables for production. Every value is server-side
# only (no NEXT_PUBLIC_), so nothing here is exposed to the browser.
#
# Nothing is strictly required to BUILD or RUN the site — each integration
# degrades gracefully when unset. But to actually capture leads, set up the
# tracker (LEADS_WEBHOOK_*) at minimum.

# --- Leads tracker (Google Sheet via Apps Script Web App) -- PRIMARY ----------
# The system of record. See scripts/leads-tracker.gs for the 3-minute setup.
LEADS_WEBHOOK_URL=
LEADS_WEBHOOK_TOKEN=

# --- Email notification (Resend) -- OPTIONAL ----------------------------------
# A per-lead email ping to your inbox, on top of the sheet. Sign up at
# resend.com, create an API key. To send to your own Gmail you can start with
# the default sender below; to send from noreply@shiftu.ca, verify the domain
# in Resend (add the DNS records it gives you).
RESEND_API_KEY=
CONTACT_TO=            # where lead emails are delivered, e.g. you@yourgmail.com
# CONTACT_FROM=Shift Ü <onboarding@resend.dev>   # default; switch to noreply@shiftu.ca after verifying the domain

# --- Website chat assistant (Anthropic) -- OPTIONAL ---------------------------
# Powers the on-site chat widget. Without it, the widget shows a graceful
# "book a call" fallback instead of an AI reply.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
